I've just released version 1.0.2 of mgmt!

> 204 files changed, 7519 insertions(+), 4040 deletions(-)

This is a new release for folks who like more obvious "stable" checkpoints.

With that, here are a few highlights from the release:

* Many cleanups make it so that mgmt should almost always shut down in ~1 sec.

* Superfluous arg graph shape issue got fixed!

* Added a bmc:firmware resource. (Thanks to Joel Rebello for the collaboration!)

* We're moving to "discussions by default" https://github.com/purpleidea/mgmt/issues/871

* We added an LLM/AI policy.

And much more...


