NEWS

* Added basic gettext support in case we want to think about translations.

* The virtualization module got a lot of improvements.

* We got a new ssh authorized_key resource.

* We moved to a more accurate, modern map implementation.

* We added an encoding package for json decoding and "flexible" json decoding.

* We added some initial stub mgmt and etcd modules for managing those in mcl.

* The exec resource now uses env everywhere by default.

* We allow duplicate exported resources.

* Add os.home and os.uid functions.

* Added an mtimes field for the exec resource.

* Added a panic() variant that takes an error message.

* A bunch of small improvements to the provisioner were done.

* Fixed a bug in the mcl grow tool code.

* Virt resource gained an autostart param.

* Embedded elastic etcd code got removed. Everything shuts down in ~1sec now. If
this is not the case, please file a discussion "bug".

* We optimized the graph shape to remove a superfluous arg.

* Added a new bmc firmware resource.

* Fixed a bug that prevented nested structs from being used in golang.template.

* Improved the hetzner:vm ecosystem and got some more testing in there.

* Fixed a bunch of incorrectly handled (but rare) error scenarios.

* Added some new string functions to the core imported "strings" library.

* CheckApply and Watch are both now wrapped with panic recovery catchers.

* Fixed the is_mac function.

* Added a func to parse floats.

* We're looking for help writing Amazon, Google, DigitalOcean, Hetzner, etc,
resources if anyone is interested, reach out to us. Particularly if there is
support from those organizations as well.

* Many other bug fixes, changes, etc...

* See the git log for more NEWS, and for anything notable I left out!


BUGS/TODO

* Function values getting _passed_ to resources doesn't work yet, but it's not a
blocker, but it would definitely be useful. We're looking into it.

* We don't have any aarch64 hardware, so no more arm64 builds or testing until
we get a donation or sponsor for that unfortunately.

* We don't have the <|> operator merged yet. Expect that when we do this, we'll
consider removing the || (default) operator. This is the only pending language
change that I know of, and these cases are easily caught by the compiler and can
be easily patched.

* Autoedge performance isn't great. It can easily be disabled. Most of the time
I just specify my edges, so this is really a convenience feature, but it should
be looked into when we have a chance.

* There was a small bug in my contrib script which mis-calculated a few
erroneous authorship numbers. This didn't affect things much, but has been
updated so that "Co-authored-by" bots aren't counted, and nobody is counted
twice.


